I highly recommend SRI DENTAL CLINIC for anyone considering dental implants or any other dental issues* *** ***** ***** *** *** ***** ******* *** *** ******* ** *** ****** and their dedication to patient care is truly commendable. Thank you for all the care.

This transparent approach gave me a clear picture of what treatment is required and its cost before hand. They use latest apps for reminder and keep you updated with your appointment and schedules from time to time.

If you are looking at a dental doctor who does not create the hype about your treatment and just sticks to the basics and treats you with almost care, then this is the clinic you should visit.

Thank you doctor.

review: When my wife had severe tooth ache and bleeding, she is also having co-morbidities ie., sugar and BP it was advised firstly to obtain x-ray of the teeth. After confirming that the patient's sugar and BP are under control and considering the x-ray, it was advised that six of the damaged teeth need to be extracted. Taking into account of the fluctuations in the sugar and BP, it was advised that the treatment need to be taken up immediately and accordingly the extraction was done immediately.  Immediately the removed dentures were supported by alternative temporary dentures. Later, the dentures were fixed in the next two or three sittings. The entire treatment was completed in six weeks during ten sittings for x-ray, extraction, temporary support and later for fixing the crowns duly grating the teeth and bridge the teeth with the support of healthy teeth.
